remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoder` provides static methods for encoding pixel data to the WebP
image format, including both single-frame and animated WebP output. WebP is a
modern image format that supports lossy and lossless compression and natively
supports transparency.

For single-frame encoding, use one of the `Encode` overloads. For animated WebP
files, build a collection of <xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderFrame> values and
pass them to `EncodeAnimated`.

This is a static class; no instances are created.

## Examples

```csharp
// Single-frame lossy WebP
using var pixmap = bitmap.PeekPixels();
var options = new SKWebpEncoderOptions(SKWebpEncoderCompression.Lossy, 80);
using var data = SKWebpEncoder.Encode(pixmap, options);
if (data != null)
    File.WriteAllBytes("output.webp", data.ToArray());
```
